{"questionId":"9074483","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A loudspeaker emits sound waves of frequency<em> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math></em> towards a metal plate that reflects the waves.&nbsp;A small microphone is moved along the line from the metal plate to the loudspeaker. The intensity&nbsp;of sound detected at the microphone as it moves varies regularly between maximum and&nbsp;minimum values.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/91d308c0898308653219ad4bf509e2e6af2611ec.png\"></p>\n<p>The speed of sound in air is 340 m s<sup>−1</sup>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Adjacent minima are separated by a distance of 0.12 m. Calculate <em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math></em>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>wavelength = 0.24 «m» ✓</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> = «<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>340</mn><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>24</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>=» 1.4 «kHz» <em><strong>OR</strong> </em>1400 «Hz» ✓</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Allow <strong>ECF</strong> from <strong>MP1</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9074483","referenceCode":"22M.2.SL.TZ2.3a.ii","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Adjacent minima are separated by a distance of 0.12 m. Calculate f.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 4: Waves","4.2 – Travelling waves","Core","Topic 4: Waves","4.5 – Standing waves","Core","Topic 4: Waves"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}